===Noun===
{{en-noun|minima|s}}

# The [[lowest]] [[limit]].
#: ''We prefer candidates with a '''minimum''' of 4 years experience in the field.''
#: ''We need a '''minimum''' of three staff members on duty at all time.''
# The [[smallest]] [[amount]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|journal=Time|title=Kate Winslet's ''Mare of Easttown'' Is the Rare Crime Drama That Cares About Its Characters|author=Judy Berman|date=April 16 2021
|passage=Realism might be the hardest aesthetic to do well. The performances have to be genuinely moving and the setting vividly evoked; bonkers twists must be kept to a '''minimum'''.
|url=https://time.com/5953833/mare-of-easttown-review/}}
#: ''He always tries to get away with doing the '''minimum'''.''
#: ''Please keep noise to a '''minimum''' after 11 o'clock''
# {{lb|en|astronomy}} A period of minimum [[brightness]] or [[energy]] [[intensity]] (of a [[star]]).
#: {{ux|en|The Maunder '''minimum''' of the Sun reportedly corresponded to a period of great cold on Earth.}}
# {{lb|en|analysis}} A [[lower bound]] of a set which is also an element of that set.
# {{lb|en|statistics}} The smallest member of a [[batch]] or [[sample]] or the lower bound of a [[probability distribution]].

